    <note type="biography">
        <p>Swiss anatomist. Taught anatomy and physiology, University of Basel, 1857–92. Professor of anatomy, Leipzig, 1872–1904. Opened a new laboratory of anatomy, 1875. Invented the microtome to slice thin tissue sections for microscopic examination, 1866.</p></note>
